		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">In <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?p=56180#56180" class="postlink">this post</a>, Memblers wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Mapper #124 is my Squeedo mapper.  Nothing emulates it though.<br /><br />Here's another list:<br /><a href="http://www.tripoint.org/kevtris/Projects/console/mappers/" class="postlink">http://www.tripoint.org/kevtris/Projects/console/mappers/</a></div>
<br />
<br />Nice site with all mapper informations, I just book-marked it. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" alt=":D" title="Very Happy" /> 
<br />
<br />Seeing from you saying '"MY" squeedo mapper', are you the one who is in charge of assigning a new mappers?
<br />If so, can you create a new mapper for the 8k PRG rom-ed games like Galaxian (Japan) from the no-intro set? These games has a very easy mapper(just 4 mirroring of 8kB) to implement, but current iNes mappers have no matching for it.  
<br />This thread at no-intro has more info about it:
<br />
<br /><a href="http://forums.no-intro.org/viewtopic.php?f=6&amp;t=1671" class="postlink">http://forums.no-intro.org/viewtopic.php?f=6&amp;t=1671</a>

		

		</td>
