	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Nope, I'm not in charge of it, I just called it mine because I designed the Squeedo mapper and board and asked for that # to be reserved years ago.
<br />
<br />The real limitation is with the iNES format specifying the size in 16kB banks.  The solution I would propose would be for an emulator to load as 8kB if the number of PRG banks is zero.  I don't know how well that proposal would go over.  Galaxian seems to be the only one like that.  But I seriously doubt anyone would make a cart that's smaller than that, so it seems like a possible solution.
<br />
<br />Better check iNES 2.0 too, to see if anything like that is specified in it.  It could already be, for all I know.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


