		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">kyuusaku wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Why does Galaxian need a new mapper to implement a hack for a non-issue? That makes no sense! Just call the mirrored ROM a verified overdump.<br /><br />Argh you ROM people annoy me, always parroting stuff like this <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" />  There are bigger issues with the iNES format, bigger issues with your scene, bigger issues with yourself, your country, your world <img src="./images/smilies/icon_wink.gif" alt=";)" title="Wink" /> There isn't a perfect way to "archive" ROMs, there never will be until we can download matter and time travel in order to get a mint copy, it's something you have to get over.</div>
<br />
<br />You are missing the point. Mirroring is not just a software issue. It DOES require extra wiring in actual hareware, at minimum. Because of this, mirrored chip and non mirrored chip is, however slight the difference is, HARDWARE-wisly different, . It is not a HACK to creat a new mappers for the hardware-wisly different chip, but was just a matter of convinience to merge similar hardwares into one mapper.
<br />
<br />I'm just saying that since we now have a certain type of chip that is not working under currunt system, let's create another mapper and wait for the emu authors to apply them.  I don't understand why you are calling this as a HACKY approach.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


