	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">kyuusaku wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I'm not missing any point. Mirroring does does not require extra wiring, it's a consequence of partial decoding, ie ignoring high address lines. Technically this is less wiring than a "standard" cart. There is already a mapper for NROM-like boards: mapper 0.<br /></div>
<br />
<br />Yes, it DOES require wiring, and you are still missing the point.
<br />In order for the mirroing to occure, the top most addresses need to be HARD-WIRED together. 
<br />
<br />You can say that the actual wire numbers are less for 8k, which is of course more roms have more pins to wire,  but what I mean by extra wiring is the Hard-Wiring requirement for the unused top address.
<br />You may consult 6502 document for the better details about how the hard-wiring works to fulfilling 16bit address ranges of 6502 with lesser memory units.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
